 faraway mists of happiness, wonder, and Easter splendor.


Translated from the Russian by Dmitri Nabokov and Peter Constantine.


*The Cyrillic letters X (Kh) and B (V) stand for Khristos vorkresye, “Christ has risen.”





THE WORD


